 I apologize for the error in my previous response. It seems that there was a mistake in the XML file format. Here is an updated version of the XML mission plan based on your requirements:
```php
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<mission>
    <name>Pistachio Tree Photography</name>
    <description>Visit 5 pistachio trees in a row and take pictures of 3 of them.</description>
    <tasks>
        <task id="1">
            <name>Start at the farm entrance</name>
            <action>Enter the farm</action>
        </task>
        <task id="2">
            <name>Visit pistachio tree 1</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
        <task id="3">
            <name>Visit pistachio tree 2</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
        <task id="4">
            <name>Visit pistachio tree 3</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
        <task id="5">
            <name>Visit pistachio tree 4</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
        <task id="6">
            <name>Visit pistachio tree 5</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
        <task id="7">
            <name>Return to the farm entrance</name>
            <action>Exit the farm</action>
        </task>
    </tasks>
    <connections>
        <connection fromTaskId="1" toTaskId="2"/>
        <connection fromTaskId="2" toTaskId="3"/>
        <connection fromTaskId="3" toTaskId="4"/>
        <connection fromTaskId="4" toTaskId="5"/>
        <connection fromTaskId="5" toTaskId="6"/>
        <connection fromTaskId="6" toTaskId="7"/>
    </connections>
</mission>
```
This XML file defines a mission with 7 tasks, including visiting the farm entrance, visiting each of the 5 pistachio trees in a row, and returning to the farm entrance. The `<tasks>` element contains all the tasks in the mission, while the `<connections>` element defines the order in which the tasks should be performed. In this case, the tasks are connected in a linear fashion, starting with task 1 and ending with task 7.

You can modify the XML file to include additional information or tasks as needed for your specific mission requirements. 